    {
      "id": "MPObject_202958094",
      "title": "Route: Man of Constant Sorrow (V5)",
      "cleanTitle": "Man of Constant Sorrow (V5)",
      "link": "https://www.mountainproject.com/route/202958094/man-of-constant-sorrow",
      "pubDate": "2026-05-11T17:49:20.000Z",
      "description": "<div class=\"fr-view\"><p>Very committing. Best to drop a rope for this one, and expect it to need some brushing as it gets very little traffic.&nbsp;</p><p>Start and climb as per Crooked Road but instead of going right, climb straight up the steep highball past small holds and a big lock-off to the top. Scope out the top before doing this line and bring all your pads and a host of spotters.</p></div><br /><img  class=\"\" src='' alt=\"\"><br><a href=\"https://www.mountainproject.com/area/105852400/virginia\">Virginia</a>\n        \n             &gt; <a href=\"https://www.mountainproject.com/area/110848199/southwest-virginia-appalachia\">Southwest Virgi&hellip;</a>\n        \n             &gt; <a href=\"https://www.mountainproject.com/area/106477419/grayson-highlands-state-park\">Grayson Highlan&hellip;</a>\n        \n             &gt; <a href=\"https://www.mountainproject.com/area/106634018/boneyard-area\">Boneyard Area</a>\n        \n             &gt; <a href=\"https://www.mountainproject.com/area/107193099/crooked-road-boulder\">Crooked Rd Boulder</a>\n    <br>Shared By: Aaron Parlier",
